        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): improve accessible session history picker",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95601.\n\nVoiceOver and keyboard users can open the Control UI chat session picker today, but the history experience was still split across partial slices: unreadable scoped session keys when labels are missing, no direct rename action in the chat picker, and sidebar recent sessions that did not expose separate switch/reopen and rename controls with clear accessible names.\n\nThis PR makes both the chat session picker and the sidebar recent-session history expose human-readable titles, timestamps, active-state text, switch/reopen controls, and rename controls through standard keyboard-focusable controls.\n\n## Summary\n\n- requests `includeDerivedTitles` for chat/recent-session loads so unlabeled conversations get readable derived titles instead of raw session keys\n- exposes each picker row as a keyboard-reachable switch action with a readable accessible name containing title, timestamp metadata, and active-state text\n- adds a keyboard-reachable rename action beside each picker row, reusing `sessions.patch` and preserving the chat-scoped refresh parameters\n- updates the sidebar recent-session list so each row exposes separate switch/reopen and rename controls with title, timestamp, and active-state announcements\n- keeps the existing New Session control reachable with its existing `aria-label`\n- updates generated locale bundles after adding the new English picker/sidebar action strings\n\n## Accessibility Notes\n\nThe picker now uses a regular list of session rows rather than an ARIA listbox. Each row contains separate, focusable controls for:\n\n- switching/reopening the session (`Switch to session: <title> · <timestamp> · Active` when current)\n- renaming the session (`Rename session: <title> · <timestamp> · Active` when current)\n\nThe sidebar recent-session history follows the same pattern: each row is a list item with a link-style switch/reopen control plus a separate rename button. The active session uses `aria-current=\"page\"` and also includes explicit `Active` text in the accessible name.\n\nThis avoids mixing ARIA `option` semantics with sibling action buttons while preserving keyboard navigation through standard links/buttons.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies derived titles render in the chat picker and the switch control accessible name includes title, timestamp metadata, and active-state text.\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies each picker row exposes a rename control and persists the new label through `sessions.patch` while retaining chat-scoped refresh parameters.\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies sidebar recent sessions expose New Session, readable title, timestamp, active state, switch/reopen, and rename accessible controls.\n- Added jsdom coverage that verifies sidebar recent-session rename uses `sessions.patch` with chat-scoped refresh parameters and derived-title loading preserved.\n- Added controller coverage for forwarding `includeDerivedTitles` and for patch refresh override preservation.\n- Ran `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts`:\n  - `ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts`: 81 passed\n  - `ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts`: 22 passed\n  - `ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`: 121 passed\n- Ran `corepack pnpm format:check ui/src/ui/app-render.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts ui/src/styles/layout.css ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.ts ui/src/ui/session-display.ts ui/src/ui/types.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.ts ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts`: passed\n- Ran `git diff --check`: passed\n\n## Not Tested\n\n- I did not run a live macOS VoiceOver pass locally. The PR adds source-level and jsdom coverage for the expected accessible names, active state, derived-title display, rename action, sidebar recent-session controls, and scoped session-list requests so the reporter can verify the branch with VoiceOver.\n",
